title: For Sale:  16ga. Pin Fire
postcontent: 16 gauge pin fire antique damascus double barrel shot gun. I cannot locate a date for this item but a year range of 1840-1860 made in Belgium. The hammers are lose, but function. The triggers are firm and function. To open the breech hammers are placed at 1/2 cock and the lock under the barrels swing to your right. Some goober decided to coat the gun with some kind of coating on the metal, and shoulder stock making it look "nice" and "preserving" the gun. The bolt connecting the hammer plates together had a new thread tapped and bolt replaced. The little tang on top of the shoulder stock is loose at the rear. Barrel condition is very nice inside considering the approximate age, some minor pitting and or rust. I have in fact fired this shotgun by modifying modern 20 gauge hulls, small pistol primers, and 15 grains of pyrodex. If you want a very classic antique that is intact and fireable this may be for you. However please consider shells are not available and the use is not convenient at all compared to modern shot guns. I was very excited to get this piece, perhaps more than any gun I have acquired in a very long time. You may have a better use for it than hanging out in the safe. Were I to keep it I was thinking of removing with aircraft stripper the coating, and replacing the shoulder stock with a very beautiful walnut crotch cut with raised cheek rest. It is time for another to enjoy this piece. Make me an offer.
